    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-04-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-04-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="63"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d63">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/521: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Oslo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-04-15">April 15,
                            1940</date>.<lb/>[Received April 15—7:31 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>91. From Cox.<note n="10" xml:id="d63fn10">Raymond E. Cox, First Secretary of
                        Legation in Norway. Cox was signing for the Ambassador, Mrs. Florence J.
                        Harriman, who after the German invasion of Norway entered Sweden on April
                        10, 1940.</note> Department’s 28, received 13.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>(2)</label>
                    <item>Estimated about 30.<note n="11" xml:id="d63fn11">In telegram No. 291, May
                            6, the Chargé in Norway informed the Department that this estimate was
                            300, not 30, but had then been reduced to 250 (340.1115A/579).</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>(3)</label>
                    <item>Evacuation American citizens dependent reopening railroad connections with
                        Sweden, no communication whatever at present with Bergen and other Norwegian
                        centers. In view of above no definite plan can be formulated.</item>
                    <label>(4)</label>
                    <item>Cooperation Berlin authorities essential.</item>
                    <label>(5)</label>
                    <item>Estimate approximately 225 requiring all or part transportation expenses
                        particularly during present banking restrictions limiting withdrawals 500
                        crowns weekly 20,000 dollars.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
